At the Final Tribal Council, Dreamz received heavy criticism from the jury: Mookie criticized him for spilling the beans about his idol, Alex berated him for lying cheating and backstabbing, Lisi Linares asked him how many zeros were in a million (which Dreamz answered correctly, much to Lisi's shock), and Boo chastised him for breaking his word on Yau-Man and promising on God that he would honor the deal. Ultimately Dreamz became the co-runner-up of the season along with Cassandra, losing to Ea

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: Minute To Win It has combined the wholesome goodness of breakfast cereal with the innate hardness of jigsaw puzzles. The front of a cereal box has been cut into sixteen squares, randomized, and must be reassembled by the contestant. The fact that all the puzzle pieces are the exact same shape adds to the difficulty. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: The average golf ball has three-hundred fifty dimples. With a delicate touch, those tiny convex curves can be aligned, and the balls can actually be stacked. In this challenge, the player will build a tower of three golf balls that must remain standing for three seconds. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: The world record for domino toppling is over four million times. In this challenge, the contestant will try their hand at CD case toppling. The twenty plastic cases must be set with care to avoid large gaps or premature tipping. A quick whoosh begins the chain reaction, which circles a red sticker/shotglass, and lands the last case in a bucket below. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: The tusks of a walrus are made of the most exquisite ivory, and yet here at Minute To Win It, they are made from coffee stirrers. In this challenge, the contestant will use these makeshift tusks to forage for marshmallows. Using a pincher-like technique, they must transfer three marshmallows from one podium to another, to create a single stack of sweetness. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: A ream of paper contains exactly five-hundred sheets. In this challenge, the contestant must balance eleven reams of paper on end. Once the giant dominoes are positioned, the contestant will trigger a chain reaction, with the last one claiming victory by landing on a bell. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: In this challenge, the contestant must create a grande burrito, substituting bed sheets for the tortilla and themselves for the delicious filling! The recipe for success is simple:Step 1: Wrap a total of five sheets.Step 2: Walk upright to center stage.Step 3: Remove all the layers to win the whole enchilada! Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

message: The distance record for throwing a playing card is just over two-hundred sixteen feet. In this challenge, the contestant must throw them for accuracy, as they attempt to stick a card into half a watermelon. This must be repeated 3 times. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: In this challenge, the contestant must simultaneously balance two eggs on inverted serving trays held in either hand. The egg's fluid contents combined with their asymmetrical shape makes for a precarious journey to their final destination. If an egg falls off, the player's hopes will be scrambled. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: In this challenge, the contestant must use four paper towel rolls and four raw eggs to construct a tower. Improper alignment will result in an uncertain collapse. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

page: Minute to Win It (American game show)
Minute to Win It (American game show)
message: A typical medium-sized pizza box is fourteen inches squared and made of cardboard. In this challenge, the contestant, using the box as a fan, must propel two raw eggs across the stage and into a predetermined zone. The unorthodox shape of the egg, however, will cause it to roll in unpredictable directions. Thus, the journey to the final destination will be a difficult one. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

message: In this challenge, the contestant, armed with rubber bands, must prove their marksmanship skills by hitting playing cards held in place with stands made of clothespins. To succeed, the player must knock down all three aces from a distance of eight feet. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

In this challenge, the contestant must swing their head in an attempt to land two tea bags attached to either side of a hat onto the bill. Both tea bags must rest on the bill in order to win. Failure to complete this task in 60 seconds may result in elimination.

What is Lepat?  Lepat is a festive rice dumpling that consists of sticky rice, peanut or red bean and coconut milk in young coconut leafy or banana leaf. It is richer in flavor compared to Lontong and also stickier.  It is wrapped in cylinder shape with string, resembling a dumpling.  Lepat is usually eaten as snacks during Hari Raya festival. What is Lemang?  Lemang is a traditional food that is often eaten at the end of fasting during Hari Raya festival. Lemang consist of glutinous rice, coconut milk and salt that are usually wrapped in banana leaves and kept in a section of bamboo tube.  The purpose of the banana leaves is to prevent the glutinous rice from sticking on the bamboo tube. Lemang are often served with Rendang and curry. What is Ketupat?  Ketupat is an Indonesia traditional dish that consists of white rice tightly packed inside young coconut leaf, woven into a diamond shape.  Ketupat is often paired with stewed meat, Rendang and curry and is easily prepared by just heating up the rice cake. Its name symbolizes “admitting of one’s mistakes” in Javanese “Ngaku Lepat” and resembles asking for forgiveness tradition during the Hari Raya festive. Until the set revamp in 2007, there was still a jack for The Phone Home Game's telephone to be plugged into on the frame of one of the show's Big Doors. Contestants calling from home would remain eligible to be in-studio contestants on The Price is Right.

page: List of The Price Is Right pricing games
message: /* The Phone Home Game */ The home viewer was called before the taping of the show began and was put on hold until the game was played. The staff reasoned that keeping someone on hold for over 20 minutes would be impolite, so the game was always played in the first half, typically no later than third.

page: List of The Price Is Right pricing games
message: /* The Phone Home Game */ There were also contestant pairings who failed to win any money, including one in which the home viewer named a product instead of a price on all three turns, thus completely wasting the game.

page: List of The Price Is Right pricing games
message: At least five pairs of players split the full $15,000 prize: on June 14, 1984 (#5374D), April 11, 1985 (#5684D), April 17, 1986 (#6084D), June 30, 1988 (#6934D), and in one episode in late 1988. There has also been at least one playing where the full $15,000 could have been won with all three correct guesses, but the studio contestant missed at least one or two.

page: List of The Price Is Right pricing games
message: /* The Phone Home Game */ During much of the 1980s, The Price is Right had a feature called "Play-Along," where viewers were invited to send postcards to the show for a chance to receive the same prizes won by the in-studio contestants. The Phone Home Game took this concept to another level, having the person whose postcard was drawn participate by telephone in a cooperative effort with the in-studio contestant to split a cash prize of up to $15,000. 游戏（二）：《金树银花满地奖金》  游戏玩法：  •每一期有2位昇菘顾客同时参加。游戏区用红线分成两个区域。  •道具树上挂有不同的奖金，共10,000元奖金。$50X40、$100X20、$200X20、$500X4  •限时45秒钟，摇树15秒，捡钱30秒。  •参加者装扮成日本相扑的大力士，同时不停摇晃摇钱树，使奖金落在地上。  •两名参加者将自己区域内的奖金拾起来，根据参加者拾取奖金数量，判定两位最后分别赢得多少奖金。

游戏（一）：《才子佳人共谱钱程》  游戏玩法：  •每集2位参赛者分别穿戴古代才子服饰，做“唐伯虎”打扮。  •现场有3个秋香的剪影。  •在透明的箱子中，装有号码01至49号的球（除了10，20，30和40），球分别有三个颜色：红、蓝与黄色。  •游戏开始，唐伯虎（参加者）会从三位中，点中一位秋香来选透明箱子的球。秋香在翩翩起舞后，从箱子中依次取出6粒绣球，由主持人念出号码，放进“聚宝盆”中。参赛者必须依照次序，记住6 组绣球的颜色与号码。例如：红12 、蓝33、黄01、蓝15、红39、蓝23。  •限时45秒，奖金是以加倍累计的方式计算。成功记住1组，可获得200元；记第二组则可获得加倍奖金$400, 然后$800, $1600, 以此类推，最高奖金$6400。若没猜中，可得安慰奖金$500。

游戏 2：1.《双龙戏珠 财源滚滚 》两组参加者  这是一个紧张而刺激的游戏，考验参加者的耐心与勇气。参加者与搭档     配合，共同完成游戏。  两个搭档手握两条细绳两端，并用细绳托起一粒金色的小球，两人可以    通过手势的高低和绳子的松紧来控制小球的走向。细绳的中间位置外侧，摆放一盏造型华丽的月光杯，参加者需要将小球从一根绳子的一侧滚落至月光杯中，从两根绳之间掉落或落地则失败。限时45秒，成功落杯一粒球奖金为$500，共10粒球，最高奖金为$5000。

游戏 1：《两代同乐  袋袋平安》两组参加者  游戏玩法：限时45秒    参加者与另一位搭档配合完成游戏，一方装扮成老人（婆婆或公公），    另一方装扮成女儿/儿子或孙子。  在舞台一端有一个放满了红包的架子，红包背后有不同的奖金:     $1000 X 2  = $2000     $   500X6   = $3000     $   300X10 = $3000   舞台另一端为一个长形桌子,拿来放 成功挟到的红包。        红包总数为18 封，最高奖金$8000
